{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"It's a great honor today"},{"time":2000,"text":"to share with you"},{"time":4000,"text":"The Digital Universe,"},{"time":6000,"text":"which was created for humanity"},{"time":8000,"text":"to really see where we are"},{"time":10000,"text":"in the universe."},{"time":13000,"text":"And so I think we can roll the video that we have."}]},{"cues":[{"time":15000,"text":"[The Himalayas.]"}]},{"cues":[{"time":18000,"text":"(Music)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":20000,"text":"The flat horizon that we've evolved with"},{"time":23000,"text":"has been a metaphor for the"},{"time":25000,"text":"infinite: unbounded resources"},{"time":27000,"text":"and unlimited capacity"},{"time":29000,"text":"for disposal of waste."},{"time":32000,"text":"It wasn't until we really"},{"time":34000,"text":"left Earth,"},{"time":36000,"text":"got above the atmosphere"},{"time":38000,"text":"and had seen the horizon"},{"time":40000,"text":"bend back on itself,"},{"time":43000,"text":"that we could understand our planet"},{"time":45000,"text":"as a limited condition."},{"time":49000,"text":"The Digital Universe Atlas"},{"time":54000,"text":"has been built"},{"time":56000,"text":"at the American Museum of Natural History"},{"time":59000,"text":"over the past 12 years."},{"time":62000,"text":"We maintain that,"},{"time":64000,"text":"put that together"},{"time":66000,"text":"as a project"},{"time":68000,"text":"to really chart the universe"},{"time":70000,"text":"across all scales."},{"time":74000,"text":"What we see here are satellites around the Earth"},{"time":77000,"text":"and the Earth in proper registration"},{"time":80000,"text":"against the universe, as we see."},{"time":87000,"text":"NASA supported this work"},{"time":89000,"text":"12 years ago"},{"time":92000,"text":"as part of the rebuilding"},{"time":94000,"text":"of the Hayden Planetarium"},{"time":96000,"text":"so that we would share this with the world."}]},{"cues":[{"time":99000,"text":"The Digital Universe is the basis"},{"time":101000,"text":"of our space show productions that we do --"},{"time":103000,"text":"our main space shows in the dome."},{"time":106000,"text":"But what you see here"},{"time":108000,"text":"is the result of, actually, internships"},{"time":110000,"text":"that we hosted with Linkoping University"},{"time":113000,"text":"in Sweden."},{"time":115000,"text":"I've had 12 students work on this"},{"time":118000,"text":"for their graduate work,"},{"time":120000,"text":"and the result has been this software called Uniview"},{"time":123000,"text":"and a company called SCISS in Sweden."},{"time":127000,"text":"This software"},{"time":129000,"text":"allows interactive use,"},{"time":132000,"text":"so this actual flight path"},{"time":134000,"text":"and movie that we see here"},{"time":136000,"text":"was actually flown live."},{"time":138000,"text":"I captured this live from my laptop"},{"time":141000,"text":"in a cafe called Earth Matters"},{"time":144000,"text":"on the Lower East Side of Manhattan, where I live,"},{"time":147000,"text":"and it was done"},{"time":149000,"text":"as a collaborative project"},{"time":151000,"text":"with the Rubin Museum of Himalayan Art"},{"time":154000,"text":"for an exhibit"},{"time":157000,"text":"on comparative cosmology."}]},{"cues":[{"time":161000,"text":"And so as we move out,"},{"time":163000,"text":"we see continuously from our planet"},{"time":166000,"text":"all the way out into the realm of galaxies, as we see here,"},{"time":169000,"text":"light-travel time, giving you a sense of how far away we are."},{"time":174000,"text":"As we move out,"},{"time":176000,"text":"the light from these distant galaxies"},{"time":178000,"text":"have taken so long,"},{"time":180000,"text":"we're essentially backing up into the past."},{"time":183000,"text":"We back so far up"},{"time":185000,"text":"we're finally seeing a containment around us --"},{"time":188000,"text":"the afterglow of the Big Bang."},{"time":190000,"text":"This is the WMAP"},{"time":192000,"text":"microwave background"},{"time":194000,"text":"that we see."},{"time":196000,"text":"We'll fly outside it here, just to see this sort of containment."},{"time":199000,"text":"If we were outside this,"},{"time":201000,"text":"it would almost be meaningless, in the sense as before time."},{"time":204000,"text":"But this our containment of the visible universe."},{"time":207000,"text":"We know the universe is bigger than that which we can see."}]},{"cues":[{"time":209000,"text":"Coming back quickly,"},{"time":211000,"text":"we see here the radio sphere that we jumped out of in the beginning,"},{"time":214000,"text":"but these are positions,"},{"time":216000,"text":"the latest positions of exoplanets"},{"time":219000,"text":"that we've mapped,"},{"time":221000,"text":"and our sun here, obviously, with our own solar system."},{"time":226000,"text":"What you're going to see -- we're going to have to jump in here pretty quickly"},{"time":229000,"text":"between several orders of magnitude"},{"time":231000,"text":"to get down to where we see the solar system --"},{"time":233000,"text":"these are the paths of"},{"time":235000,"text":"Voyager 1, Voyager 2, Pioneer 11 and Pioneer 10,"},{"time":238000,"text":"the first four spacecraft to have left the solar system."},{"time":243000,"text":"Coming in closer,"},{"time":245000,"text":"picking up Earth,"},{"time":249000,"text":"orbit of the Moon, and we see the Earth."},{"time":255000,"text":"This map can be updated,"},{"time":258000,"text":"and we can add in new data."}]},{"cues":[{"time":260000,"text":"I know Dr. Carolyn Porco is the camera P.I."},{"time":262000,"text":"for the Cassini mission."},{"time":264000,"text":"But here we see the complex trajectory"},{"time":266000,"text":"of the Cassini mission"},{"time":268000,"text":"color coded for different mission phases,"},{"time":270000,"text":"ingeniously developed so that"},{"time":272000,"text":"45 encounters with the largest moon, Titan,"},{"time":274000,"text":"which is larger that the planet Mercury,"},{"time":276000,"text":"diverts the orbit into different parts of mission phase."}]},{"cues":[{"time":281000,"text":"This software allows us to come close"},{"time":283000,"text":"and look at parts of this."},{"time":286000,"text":"This software can also be networked between domes."},{"time":289000,"text":"We have a growing user base of this,"},{"time":291000,"text":"and we network domes."},{"time":293000,"text":"And we can network between domes and classrooms."},{"time":297000,"text":"We're actually sharing tours of the universe"},{"time":300000,"text":"with the first sub-Saharan"},{"time":302000,"text":"planetarium in Ghana"},{"time":304000,"text":"as well as"},{"time":306000,"text":"new libraries that have been built"},{"time":308000,"text":"in the ghettos in Columbia"},{"time":310000,"text":"and a high school"},{"time":312000,"text":"in Cambodia."},{"time":314000,"text":"And the Cambodians have"},{"time":316000,"text":"actually controlled the Hayden Planetarium from their high school."}]},{"cues":[{"time":320000,"text":"This is an image from Saturday,"},{"time":322000,"text":"photographed by the Aqua satellite, but through the Uniview software."},{"time":325000,"text":"So you're seeing the edge of the Earth."},{"time":327000,"text":"This is Nepal."},{"time":329000,"text":"This is, in fact, right here is the valley of Lhasa,"},{"time":332000,"text":"right here in Tibet."},{"time":335000,"text":"But we can see the haze"},{"time":337000,"text":"from fires and so forth in the Ganges valley"},{"time":339000,"text":"down below in India."},{"time":341000,"text":"This is Nepal and Tibet."}]},{"cues":[{"time":345000,"text":"And just in closing,"},{"time":348000,"text":"I'd just like to say this beautiful world that we live on --"},{"time":353000,"text":"here we see a bit of the snow"},{"time":355000,"text":"that some of you may have had to brave in coming out --"},{"time":360000,"text":"so I'd like to just say"},{"time":362000,"text":"that what the world needs now"},{"time":364000,"text":"is a sense of being able to"},{"time":366000,"text":"look at ourselves in this much larger condition now"},{"time":369000,"text":"and a much larger sense of what home is."},{"time":372000,"text":"Because our home is the universe,"},{"time":374000,"text":"and we are the universe, essentially."},{"time":376000,"text":"We carry that in us."},{"time":378000,"text":"And to be able to see our context"},{"time":381000,"text":"in this larger sense at all scales"},{"time":384000,"text":"helps us all, I think, in understanding"},{"time":386000,"text":"where we are and who we are in the universe."}]},{"cues":[{"time":388000,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":390000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}